# Environment Variables Template for Azure App Service

## Copy this template and fill in values in Azure Portal

**Backend App Service → Configuration → Application settings**

### Core

```
NODE_ENV=production
PORT=3000
API_PREFIX=api/v1
```

### Database (from Step 3)

```
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://linkerpro:YourStrongPassword123!@linker-pro-db.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/linker_pro?sslmode=require
```

### Optional Appwrite mirror (PostgreSQL remains primary)

```
APPWRITE_MIRROR_ENABLED=false
APPWRITE_ENDPOINT=https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1
APPWRITE_PROJECT_ID=your_appwrite_project_id
APPWRITE_API_KEY=your_appwrite_api_key
APPWRITE_DATABASE_ID=your_appwrite_database_id
APPWRITE_COLLECTION_PREFIX=lp_
```

### Redis (from Step 4)

```
REDIS_HOST=linker-pro-cache.redis.cache.windows.net
REDIS_PORT=6380
REDIS_PASSWORD=YOUR_REDIS_PRIMARY_KEY_HERE
REDIS_TLS=true
```

### JWT Secrets (generate new ones)

```bash
# Generate random 32-byte secrets:
openssl rand -base64 32
```

```
JWT_SECRET=random_32_byte_base64_string_here
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=another_random_32_byte_string
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=15m
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRES_IN=7d
```

### Encryption (32-char hex key)

```bash
# Generate:
openssl rand -hex 16
```

```
ENCRYPTION_KEY=your_32_character_hex_key_string_here
```

### OpenAI (get API key from https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)

```
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here
```

### Frontend & Webhooks

```
FRONTEND_URL=https://linker-pro-frontend.azurewebsites.net
WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=https://linker-pro-backend.azurewebsites.net/api/v1/webhooks
```

### Platform OAuth Credentials

Get these from each platform's developer dashboard:

#### Shopify

```
SHOPIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_shopify_app_id
SHOPIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_shopify_app_secret
SHOPIFY_SCOPES=read_products,write_products,read_inventory,write_inventory,read_orders
```

#### Salla

```
SALLA_CLIENT_ID=your_salla_app_id
SALLA_CLIENT_SECRET=your_salla_app_secret
SALLA_SCOPES=offline_access
```

#### Amazon SP-API

```
AMAZON_CLIENT_ID=your_amazon_app_id
AMAZON_CLIENT_SECRET=your_amazon_app_secret
AMAZON_IAM_ARN=arn:aws:iam::123456789:role/yourRole
```

#### Zid

```
ZID_CLIENT_ID=your_zid_app_id
ZID_CLIENT_SECRET=your_zid_app_secret
```

#### TikTok Shop

```
TIKTOK_APP_KEY=your_tiktok_app_key
TIKTOK_APP_SECRET=your_tiktok_app_secret
```

#### eBay

```
EBAY_CLIENT_ID=your_ebay_app_id
EBAY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_ebay_app_secret
```

#### Etsy

```
ETSY_API_KEY=your_etsy_api_key
ETSY_SHARED_SECRET=your_etsy_shared_secret
```

#### Walmart

```
WALMART_CLIENT_ID=your_walmart_merchant_id
WALMART_CLIENT_SECRET=your_walmart_client_secret
```

#### MercadoLibre

```
MERCADOLIBRE_CLIENT_ID=your_ml_app_id
MERCADOLIBRE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_ml_app_secret
```

#### AliExpress

```
ALIEXPRESS_APP_KEY=your_aliexpress_app_key
ALIEXPRESS_APP_SECRET=your_aliexpress_app_secret
```

#### WooCommerce & Magento

These are per-store, not global. Add credentials in the app when connecting.

---

## Add to Azure CLI

All at once:

```bash
az webapp config appsettings set \
  --resource-group linker-pro-rg \
  --name linker-pro-backend \
  --settings \
    NODE_ENV=production \
    PORT=3000 \
    DATABASE_URL="postgresql://linkerpro:YourStrongPassword123!@linker-pro-db.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/linker_pro?sslmode=require" \
    REDIS_HOST=linker-pro-cache.redis.cache.windows.net \
    REDIS_PORT=6380 \
    REDIS_PASSWORD=YOUR_REDIS_PRIMARY_KEY \
    REDIS_TLS=true \
    JWT_SECRET=GENERATED_SECRET \
    JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=GENERATED_SECRET \
    ENCRYPTION_KEY=GENERATED_KEY \
    OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key \
    FRONTEND_URL=https://linker-pro-frontend.azurewebsites.net \
    WEBHOOK_BASE_URL=https://linker-pro-backend.azurewebsites.net/api/v1/webhooks
```
